whatsapp_content:
Hi Shreyam, This is Vaibhav (Senior GMAT Strategy and Subject Matter expert at e-GMAT). How are you?

I got your request for study plan. 645+ is a great target for ISB. For this, you need to achieve a sum of scores (V + Q + D) of 246.

Considering you are struggling in all three sections, we should surely work towards fixing this and building a strong foundation across Verbal, Quant, and Data Insights.

We can go for a balanced strategy - for example, we can target V82, Q83, D81 - all around 74-83rd percentiles.

Or we can also go for a Verbal driven strategy with V84, Q83, D79 (aiming for 89th percentile in Verbal and around 76-80th percentiles in Quant and Data Insights) OR a Quant driven strategy with V81, Q84, D81 (aiming for 85th percentile in Quant and around 66-83rd percentiles in Verbal and Data Insights).

What would be your preference - do you feel more comfortable with numbers or with reading and reasoning? This will help us choose the best strategy for you.

2. Verbal Driven Strategy: V86, Q85, D84 (targeting 96th percentile in Verbal)

3. Quant Driven Strategy: V85, Q86, D84 (aiming for 91st percentile in Quant)

Which approach feels more natural to you - focusing more on Verbal or Quant, or keeping it balanced across all sections?

Hi Rohilb,

Your Assigned Mentor

Mr. Amruth

üí¨ Connect on WhatsApp

By the way, 735+ is a perfect target for M7 schools. For this, you need to achieve a sum of scores (V + Q + D) of 259.

Considering you are struggling with Critical Reasoning in Verbal, we should surely work towards fixing this and get you to at least V86 (96th percentile) or higher from your current level. This is crucial since Verbal is your weak area.

üìä Recommended Score Strategy:

üéØ Quant Driven Strategy

Given that you are relatively stronger in Quant, this strategy leverages your strength while improving Verbal to a competitive level.

Quant: Q90 (100th percentile)
Data Insights: D84 (97th percentile)
Verbal: V85 (94th percentile)

Your mentor will discuss this in great detail during the meeting and set you up with a plan of action to bridge the gap from your current 665+ to the target 735+.

We look forward to the discussion.

Regards,

Rajat Sadana

Hi Vinusha,

üí¨ Connect on WhatsApp

By the way, 705+ is a perfect target for ISB. For this, you need to achieve a sum of scores (V + Q + D) of 255.

Considering you are starting fresh and need to build proficiency in all three sections, we have multiple strategic approaches depending on your natural strengths:
